	This comprehensive User Flow Diagram illustrates the seamless, intuitive journey of users interacting with the Enroute career navigation platform, showcasing how the system guides users from initial app launch through to confident career decision-making. The diagram is structured around five core navigation areas (Home, Path, Dahlia, Career Swipe, and Profile) with clear directional arrows that map every possible user path through the platform.

The user journey begins with the Splash Screen followed by a structured Onboarding Process that includes account creation (with three phases: account details, AI persona selection, and personalization) or sign-in. Upon successful authentication, users are directed to the Home Screen via a personalized welcome modal. The Onboarding process is designed to be efficient while collecting essential data for personalization, with the AI persona selection (male, female, or neutral) and career interest input directly informing the system's recommendation engine.

The Home Screen serves as the central hub with five primary features: Record Idea (for voice-based career ideas), Take Career Aptitude Test (20-question assessment covering work style, skills, knowledge, and values), Build Roadmap (step-by-step planning with skill gap analysis), Scan CV (AI-powered resume analysis with skill recommendations), and Library (centralized storage for all user-generated content). This screen also displays the user's activity history and provides quick access to all major features.

The Path Screen enables users to search for specific skills and roles, with detailed learning modules organized around career paths. Each learning module includes role overviews (job demand, salary ranges, completion time), learning materials (PDFs, videos), and user reviews. The system intelligently recommends relevant modules based on the user's profile and progress, with a focus on practical, career-advancing content.

The Dahlia AI Interface provides a rich conversational experience where users can interact with the AI mentor through voice or text. The voice interface includes live transcription with adjustable settings, while the text interface supports file sharing. Users can take notes during conversations, switch AI personas mid-conversation, and review call summaries with key insights and quotes. After each conversation, the system generates a detailed summary with actionable recommendations and learning resources.

The Career Swipe Interface presents job opportunities in a card-based format that aligns with Gen Z's preference for visual, low-friction interactions. Each card displays company name, location, match percentage, role details, required skills, and salary range. The swipe mechanic (right for interest, left for dismissal) creates an intuitive interaction pattern that respects users' attention spans while collecting valuable preference data for future recommendations.

The Profile Screen consolidates user information, achievements, and settings in one location. Users can view their top job matches, skill completion rates, and career progress. The profile section includes comprehensive settings for notifications, privacy, and account management, with features like 2FA, data sharing controls, and profile visibility options.

