Data Store Mapping

The DFD explicitly maps all data flows to the corresponding ERD tables, creating a seamless connection between logical data design and functional processes. Each of the 20 data stores (D1-D20) corresponds directly to an entity in the ERD, ensuring data consistency across the system. This mapping creates a clear traceability from user actions to data storage:

* User identity & preferences: profiles (D1), user\_settings (D2)  
